    • Method Detail

      • getWireLength

        @Nonnegative
int getWireLength()
        Returns the wire length of this packet. This must be exact, and not an overestimate. If toWire(java.nio.ByteBuffer) writes fewer bytes than the computed length, the base class will assume error in the serializer and throw an exception.
